    "description": "<span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2295070/extras/7af26d54cb2e5573051d1e6801b8b9d6.avif?t=1762455906\" width=616 height=100 /></span><br><br><i>In support of Project Gutenberg, a volunteer effort to digitize, archive, and distribute works of literature</i><br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Decode a vast and varied collection of curated poetry, where each poem is encrypted using one of the world's oldest codes: <strong>the substitution cipher</strong><br></li><li>Decrypt over <strong>400 excerpts</strong> as you explore <strong>classic poetic themes</strong> ranging from the bliss of love to the depths of despair <br></li><li>Like what you decoded? Read the entire poem in-game or download each poet's anthology online <i>for free</i>, direct links included!<br></li><li>Share the joy of poetry--10% of every sale is donated to Project Gutenberg, an online library of over 60,000 free ebooks<br></li><li>Play at your own pace with four difficulty settings to choose from<br></li><li>Relax with a soothing, contemplative soundtrack<br></li><li>Choose between night or sunlight mode with optional enlarged cipher text</li></ul><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><i>&quot;Poetry is a deal of joy and pain and wonder, with a dash of the dictionary.&quot;</i> - Khalil Gibran</h2><br><br>Content note: This game features classic works of poetry and brief biographies of poets. Certain biographies and poems contain non-graphic references to violence, drugs, sex, and suicide.",
